http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/OISCA-scholarship-for-two-students/article13983258.ece

: Abhiram A.P., a student of St. Joseph’s Junior School in Kozhikode, and Sandra Aleena Jose of Infant Jesus English Medium School in Thiruvambady have been selected for the OISCA International Scholarship that enables them to have their higher secondary education at the OISCA Academy in Japan. They have been selected from hundreds of applicants who completed the SSLC examination in 2015.They will leave for Japan in April.OISCA South India chapter has sent 33 students for Higher Secondary Education in Japan over 14 years, a press release said. — Staff Reporter